    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single deficient factor (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) reflects testing at only one ASTM F1717 offset distance. This gap is offset by strong output comparison results (all E/uval < 1.96, all QoI differences < 10%), two-laboratory test program, and direct equivalency of validation specimens to the COU device. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level determination and acceptance of the FEA model for the stated COU.",
